- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper explores the use of domain-adversarial learning as a regularizer to avoid overfitting.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the projection of word-vectors into a common space, which is a technique used in computer vision tasks.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with text classification, which is a subfield of information retrieval.
